Class InputValidator

java.lang.Object
com.SC2002.bto.utils.InputValidator
public class InputValidator extends Object
InputValidator contains methods for validating user input such as NRIC, password formats, age requirements, and marital status.

    • validateNric

      public static boolean validateNric(String nric)
      Validates the provided NRIC. The valid NRIC should start with 'S' or 'T', followed by 7 digits and end with a letter.
      Parameters:
      nric - the NRIC string to validate.
      Returns:
      true if the NRIC is valid; false otherwise.

    • validatePassword

      public static boolean validatePassword(String pw)
      Validates the provided password. This method checks if the password is non-null and meets the minimum length requirement.
      Parameters:
      password - the password to validate.
      Returns:
      true if the password is valid; false otherwise.

    • isDefaultPassword

      Parameters:

    • validateSingleApplicantAge

      public static boolean validateSingleApplicantAge(int age, String maritalStatus)
